ther2"><title>Democratic Republic of the Congo, Ethiopia, United Republic of Tanzania</title><sec><title>Monitoring vital events </title><p>Gustavo Corr&#x000ea;a et al. (306&#x02013;308) argue for broader use of immunization data.</p></sec></sec><sec sec-type="other3"><title>India</title><sec><title>A decade&#x02019;s progress</title><p>Suman Chakrabarti et al. (270&#x02013;282) analyse equity and coverage of child services.</p></sec></sec><sec sec-type="other4"><title>Global</title><sec><title>Where there are no surgeons</title><p>Bhargava Mullapudi et al. (254&#x02013;258) estimate gaps in access to pediatric surgery.</p></sec><sec><title>Antimicrobial resistance surveillance</title><p>C&#x000e9;cile Aenishaenslin et al. (283&#x02013;289) point out that better evidence is needed. </p></sec><sec><title>Documenting maternal and child health </title><p>Keiko Osaki and Hirotsugu Aiga (296&#x02013;305) argue for the adaption of home-based records.</p></sec><sec><title>Unhealthy food and drink at sporting events</title><p>Robin Ireland et al. (290&#x02013;296) call for scrutiny of sponsorship and advertising.</p></sec></sec></body></article>